HEADWORD: Sabbaton
<hw>Sab"ba*ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>zapaton</ets>, a large shoe, F. <ets>sabot</ets> a wooden
shoe.]</ety> <def>A round-toed, armed covering for the feet, worn during
a part of the sixteenth century in both military and civil
dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

